'''Carney Chibueze Chukwuemeka''' ({{Audio|LL-Q33578_(ibo)-Goodymeraj-Carney_Chibueze_Chukwuemeka.wav|pronunciation|help=no}}; born 20 October 2003) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[left winger]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].

Born in Vienna, he represented England at youth level. In 2026, he committed to play for his birth country of [[Austria national football team|Austria]].

A product of the [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] and [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] academies, Chukwuemeka made his debut for the latter club's first team in 2021, before signing for Chelsea in 2022.<ref>{{cite web |title=Carney Chukwuemeka – Profile |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/players/u23/carneychukwuemeka |url-status=live |access-date=19 May 2021 |publisher=Aston Villa F.C. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210519195709/https://www.avfc.co.uk/players/u23/carneychukwuemeka/ |archive-date=19 May 2021 }}</ref>

==Club career==
===Aston Villa===
Chukwuemeka joined the [[Aston Villa F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Aston Villa academy]] from the [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] academy in March 2016.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Maston |first=Tom |date=15 April 2021 |title=Carney Chukwuemeka: Aston Villa wonderkid that Europe's top clubs are queuing up to sign |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/carney-chukwuemeka-aston-villa-wonderkid-europe-top-clubs/1rfzq9h0qmjip1gs8j6glmyev5 |url-status=live |access-date=19 May 2021 |publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416174635/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/carney-chukwuemeka-aston-villa-wonderkid-europe-top-clubs/1rfzq9h0qmjip1gs8j6glmyev5 |archive-date=16 April 2021 }}</ref><ref name="debut">{{Cite web |last1=Watson |first1=Chris |last2=Cusack |first2=Richard |date=15 May 2021 |title=Carney Chukwuemeka – transfer talk, contract and Villa plan |url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/carney-chukwuemeka-aston-villa-transfer-20603848 |access-date=22 May 2021 |website=[[BirminghamLive]]}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract with Villa in July 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Preece|first=Ashley|date=27 July 2020|title=Aston Villa tie down 'best 16-year-old in England' Chukwuemeka|url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/aston-villa-carney-chukwuemeka-liverpool-18671981|access-date=19 May 2021|website=BirminghamLive}}</ref>

Chukwuemeka made his senior debut for the team on 19 May 2021 in a 2–1 away victory over [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], hitting the post within minutes of entering the game.<ref name="debut" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=Tottenham 1–2 Aston Villa: Sloppy Spurs beaten on fans' return to leave European hopes under threat|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/tottenham-hotspur-vs-aston-villa/report/429205|access-date=19 May 2021|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]|last=Brand|first=Gerard|date=20 May 2021}}</ref> On 23 May 2021, he was named Aston Villa Academy Player of the Season for the [[2020–21 Aston Villa F.C. season|2020–21 season]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=23 May 2021|title=Martinez voted Supporters' Player of the Season 🏆|url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2021/may/Martinez-voted-Supporters-Player-of-the-Season-/|url-status=live|access-date=2021-05-23|website=Aston Villa Football Club|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523153651/https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2021/may/Martinez-voted-Supporters-Player-of-the-Season-/ |archive-date=23 May 2021 }}</ref> The following day, Chukwuemeka was part of the Aston Villa U18s squad that won the [[FA Youth Cup]], beating [[Liverpool F.C. Reserves and Academy|Liverpool U18s]] 2–1 in the final.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Preece|first=Ashley|date=2021-05-24|title=Aston Villa vs Liverpool FA Youth Cup final LIVE updates|url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/match-reports/aston-villa-youth-cup-liverpool-20666405|access-date=2021-05-24|website=BirminghamLive|archive-date=27 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220527092508/https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/match-reports/aston-villa-youth-cup-liverpool-20666405|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Chukwuemeka made his first senior start on 24 August 2021 in a 6–0 victory against [[Barrow F.C.|Barrow]] in the second round of the EFL Cup, and made his first league start four days later in a 1–1 draw with [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]], a performance [[Paul Merson]] hailed as "outstanding", adding "he will be an absolute star".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mir|first=Amir|date=2021-08-29|title=Paul Merson delivers verdict on Chukwuemeka's performance for Aston Villa v Brentford|url=https://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2021/08/29/paul-merson-delivers-verdict-on-chukwuemekas-performance-for-aston-villa-v-brentford/|access-date=2021-08-30|website=HITC}}</ref>

===Chelsea===
On 2 August 2022, Aston Villa and [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] confirmed that the clubs had reached an agreement for the permanent transfer of Chukwuemeka, subject to the player agreeing personal terms and undergoing a medical.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2022/august/02/aston-villa-agree-chukwuemeka-departure/|title=Aston Villa agree Chukwuemeka departure|work=Aston Villa FC|date=2 August 2022|access-date=2 August 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/chukwuemeka-transfer-agreed|title=Chukwuemeka transfer agreed|work=Chelsea FC|date=2 August 2022|access-date=2 August 2022}}</ref> On 4 August 2022, Chelsea announced the signing of Chukwuemeka on a six-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/chukwuemeka-signing-confirmed|title=Chukwuemeka signing confirmed|work=Chelsea FC|date=4 August 2022|access-date=4 August 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62398766|title=Carney Chukwuemeka: Chelsea sign Aston Villa midfielder for £20m|publisher=BBC Sport|date=4 August 2022|access-date=27 June 2023}}</ref> On 20 August 2023, Chukwuemeka scored his first senior goal in a 3–1 loss to [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]], and was later substituted after suffering a knee injury.<ref>{{Cite web |title=West Ham 3-1 Chelsea: Mauricio Pochettino still waiting for first victory as Blues manager |work=Sky Sports |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12309/12941711/west-ham-3-1-chelsea-mauricio-pochettino-still-waiting-for-first-win-as-blues-boss |access-date=2023-09-04 }}</ref>

=== Borussia Dortmund ===
On 3 February 2025, [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] signed Chukwuemeka on loan until the end of the season, with an option to make the move permanent.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Carney Chukwuemeka joins Borussia Dortmund on loan from Chelsea |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/carney-chukwuemeka-borussia-dortmund-loan-chelsea-30335 |access-date=2025-02-03 |website=www.bundesliga.com}}</ref> On 5 April, he netted his first goal for the club in a 4–1 away win over [[SC Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Berger |first=Patrick |url=https://sport.sky.de/fussball/artikel/carney-chukwuemeka-begeistert-beim-bvb-ein-schluessel-fuer-weg-nach-europa/13343787/35311 |title=Carney Chukwuemeka begeistert beim BVB - ein Schlüssel für Weg nach Europa? |publisher=Sky Sport |language=de |date=7 April 2025 }}</ref> On 26 August, Chukwuemeka joined Borussia Dortmund on a permanent transfer.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Carney Chukwuemeka departs for Borussia Dortmund |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/carney-chukwuemeka-departs-for-borussia-dortmund |access-date=2025-08-26 |website=www.chelseafc.com}}</ref> Later that year, on 1 October, he scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 4–1 win over [[Athletic Bilbao]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Emons |first=Michael |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c784vgq71eet |title=Borussia Dortmund 4–1 Athletic Club |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 October 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Chukwuemeka was eligible to play for the national teams of [[Austria national football team|Austria]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Guyett |first=Matthew |date=2023-04-26 |title=Chelsea midfielder approached by Austria to switch national team – Reports |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/rumor-chelsea-midfielder-approached-austria-switch-national-team-reports |access-date=2023-06-28 |website=sportskeeda.com}}</ref> [[France national football team|France]],<ref>{{Cite news |last=Silas |first=Don |date=2024-09-04 |title='My mother is from France' - Chukwuemeka on why he snubbed France, England |url=https://dailypost.ng/2024/09/04/my-mother-is-from-france-antoine-on-why-he-snubbed-england-france/ |location=Lagos, Nigeria|access-date=2025-04-05 |newspaper=[[Daily Post (Nigeria)|Daily Post]]|language=en-US |archive-date=10 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240910113312/https://dailypost.ng/2024/09/04/my-mother-is-from-france-olise-on-why-he-snubbed-england-france/ |url-status=live }}</ref> [[England national football team|England]], and [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name="AllNigeriaRio">{{cite web |url=https://allnigeriasoccer.com/super-eagles-dual-nationals-xi-featuring-arsenal-liverpool-chelsea-burnley-leicester-stars |title=SUPER EAGLES DUAL NATIONALS XI FEATURING ARSENAL, LIVERPOOL, CHELSEA, BURNLEY, LEICESTER STARS |website=All Nigeria Soccer |date=29 October 2025 |access-date=21 November 2025}}</ref> After making two appearances for [[Nigeria national under-17 football team|England U17]] national team, on 29 March 2021, he made his debut for the [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]] squad in 2–0 victory over [[Wales national under-18 football team|Wales]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Keen |first=Liam |date=29 March 2021 |title=Villa young Lions roar for England |url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/football/aston-villa/2021/03/29/villa-young-lions-roar-for-england/ |url-status=live |access-date=19 May 2021 |website=[[Express & Star]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210519200541/https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/football/aston-villa/2021/03/29/villa-young-lions-roar-for-england/ |archive-date=19 May 2021 }}</ref>

On 2 September 2021, Chukwuemeka made his debut for the [[England national under-19 football team|England U19s]] during a 2–0 victory over [[Italy national under-19 football team|Italy U19s]] at [[St George's Park National Football Centre|St. George's Park]], he also captained the side.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2021/Sep/02/20210209-england-mu19s-2-0-italy-report|title=England MU19s 2-0 Italy|first=Nicholas|last=Veevers|date=2 September 2021|accessdate=3 September 2021|website=EnglandFootball.com}}</ref> On 10 November 2021, he scored his first goal at this level, in a 4–0 victory over [[Andorra national under-19 football team|Andorra U19]] in a [[2022 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification]] match.<ref>{{cite web |title=England-Andorra {{!}} Under-19|url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/match/2031116--england-vs-andorra/?iv=true|publisher=UEFA|access-date=10 November 2021}}</ref>

On 17 June 2022, Chukwuemeka was named in the England squad for the [[2022 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|2022 UEFA European Under-19 Championship finals]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 June 2022 |title=Aston Villa trio named in England squad for U19 Euros |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2022/june/17/trio-named-in-/ |access-date=2022-06-17 |website=Aston Villa Football Club}}</ref> Chukwuemeka featured in every game of their tournament, scoring in group stage victories against [[Austria national under-19 football team|Austria]] and [[Serbia national under-19 football team|Serbia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12040/12642651/meet-englands-young-lions-gunning-for-glory-in-under-19s-european-championships-final-against-israel|title=Meet England's Young Lions gunning for glory in Under-19s European Championships final against Israel|first=Zinny|last=Boswell|date=1 July 2022|accessdate=13 July 2022|publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> On 1 July 2022, he scored the second goal in England's 3–1 extra time victory over [[Israel national under-19 football team|Israel]] in the final.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/news/0277-1585addeb047-8422a993d714-1000--israel-1-3-england-aet-chukwuemeka-and-ramsey-the-extra-time-he/|title=Israel 1-3 England (aet): Chukwuemeka and Ramsey the extra-time heroes as Young Lions fight back|publisher=UEFA |first=Sam|last=Honeyman|date=1 July 2022 |access-date=19 November 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12642555/israel-u19-1-3-england-u19-aet-young-lions-stage-extra-time-fightback-to-win-european-championship|title=Israel U19 1-3 England U19 (AET): Young Lions come from behind to win European Championship|first=Dan|last=Sansom|date=1 July 2022|accessdate=1 July 2022|publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> His performances during the competition led to his inclusion in the UEFA team of the tournament.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/news/0277-158d3934d81a-206a691b8c37-1000--u19-euro-team-of-the-tournament/|title=2022 Under-19 EURO Team of the Tournament|publisher=UEFA|date=5 July 2022|access-date=13 July 2022}}</ref>

On 21 September 2022, Chukwuemeka made his [[England national under-20 football team|England U20]] debut during a 3–0 victory over [[Chile national under-20 football team|Chile]] at the [[Pinatar Arena]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2022/Sep/21/england-mu20s-chile-pinatar-match-report-20222109|title=Report: England MU20s 3-0 Chile|first=Liam|last=Crane|date=21 September 2022|accessdate=25 September 2022|website=EnglandFootball.com}}</ref> On 10 May 2023, Chukwuemeka was included in the England squad for the [[2023 FIFA U-20 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2023/May/11/england-mu20s-squad-named-for-fifa-u20-world-cup-in-argentina-20231005|title=England MU20s squad named for World Cup in Argentina|first=Nick|last=Veevers|date=10 May 2023|accessdate=1 June 2023|website=EnglandFootball.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65558532|title=Fifa Under-20 World Cup: England name squad for tournament|publisher=BBC Sport|date=11 May 2023|access-date=27 June 2023}}</ref> However, he didn't arrive at the tournament until after the group stages due to his club commitments.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/chelsea-fc-carney-chukwuemeka-joins-england-under-20-world-cup-b1084287.html|title=Chelsea midfielder Carney Chukwuemeka jets off to join England squad at the Under-20 World Cup|first=Nizaar|last=Kinsella|date=29 May 2023|accessdate=1 June 2023|website=Evening Standard|location=London}}</ref> His only appearance of the tournament saw him start in their round of sixteen defeat against [[Italy national under-20 football team|Italy]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/669416|title=Italy oust England at U20 World Cup thanks to late penalty|publisher=ESPN|date=1 June 2023|access-date=27 June 2023}}</ref>

In March 2024, Chukwuemeka received his first call-up to the [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]] squad for their matches against Azerbaijan and Luxembourg.<ref name="EnglandSquad">{{cite web |url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2024/Mar/15/england-mens-under-21s-squad-named-for-azerbaijan-and-luxembourg-games-in-march-20241503 |title=England men's under-21s squad named for Azerbaijan and Luxembourg games in March 2024 |website=England Football |date=15 March 2024 |access-date=21 November 2025}}</ref> However, he was unable to feature in either match as he withdrew from the squad due to a knock sustained while on international duty.<ref name="ChelseaKnock">{{cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/internationals-madueke-on-target-in-u21s-victory |title=Internationals: Madueke on target in U21s victory |website=Chelsea Football Club |date=22 March 2024 |access-date=21 November 2025}}</ref>

On 9 March 2026, Chukwuemeka's request to his switch international allegiance to Austria was approved by FIFA.<ref name="knowledge.fifa.com">{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform}}</ref> On 27 March 2026, he made his debut in a friendly in [[Vienna]] against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]], and scored his team's 4th goal in an eventual 5-1 victory.<ref name="knowledge.fifa.com"/>

==Personal life==
Chukwuemeka was born in [[Vienna]],<ref>{{Cite web |title="Aufgeregt und dankbar" – Carney Chukwuemeka im Interview |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/de/aktuelles/news/news.html/2025/2/3/Aufgeregt-und-dankbar-Carney-Chukwuemeka-im-Interview.html |access-date=2026-02-13 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> Austria, to Nigerian parents and was raised in Northampton, England.<ref name="GoalBio">{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/carney-chukwuemeka-aston-villa-wonderkid-europe-top-clubs/1rfzq9h0qmjip1gs8j6glmyev5 |title=Carney Chukwuemeka: Aston Villa wonderkid that Europe's top clubs are queuing up to sign |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |author=Maston, Tom |date=15 April 2021 |access-date=21 November 2025}}</ref> His older brother, [[Caleb Chukwuemeka|Caleb]], is also a professional footballer who came through the academy at [[Northampton Town]] and was previously on the books of [[Aston Villa]].

He attended St James CofE primary school in Northampton and then [[Northampton School for Boys]] with his brother.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Townley |first1=John |title='A different level, 93 goals, six hat-tricks' – The making of Aston Villa's Chukwuemeka brothers |url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/carney-chukwuemeka-aston-villa-gerrard-21481911 |website=[[Birmingham Mail]] |date=15 December 2021 |access-date=15 August 2022}}</ref>

